ba431374-9454-5374-b794-3cf50311bfd1,tg:rubgr:867,e73_Descriptions,,id.desc,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"[recto] Ad [Addendum] Bruegel: Way to Calvary. Compositionally close to Bles: Doria Pamphilj and Vienna Akademie. City on the left, Rock in centre, place of execution, surrounded by crowd, on right. Movement of people around the central path, many figures & horses seen from the back and including peddlar with load on his back seen from the back. Women carrying loads on their heads Christ in distance breaking down under the cross [schema] cf. also Corn. Massys, Way to Calvary, Hluboka ([Heinrich Gerhard] Franz, [= Niederländische Landschaftsmalerei im Zeitalter des Manierismus, Graz: Akademische Druck- u[nd] Verlagsanstalt], fig. 114, text p. 95 f.) but from right to left, also peddlar! Children tiny Christ breaking down under cross. Corn. Massys (?) Brussels (Franz, p. 96, fig. 116) with mourners on right, round church Jerusalem, children;

[verso] For the disposition of the reds see also the Way to Calvary (by the Brunsw[ich] Monogr[ammist]?) in Basel (Franz, Colour pl. 15).[scan]",descriptive note,Nederlands,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
